title.rendered: Dubai vs Emirates, International T20 League 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Dubai: George Munsey, Robin Uthappa (wk), Sikandar Raza, Rovman Powell (c), Dasun Shanaka, Yusuf Pathan, Chamika Karunaratne, Hazrat Luqman, Adam Zampa, Akif Raja, Fred Klaassen

Emirates: Andre Fletcher, Muhammad Waseem, Nicholas Pooran, Lorcan Tucker (wk), Kieron Pollard (c), Dwayne Bravo, Dan Mousley, Trent Boult, Imran Tahir, Fazalhaq Farooqi, Zahoor Khan

Pitch Report

Venue: Dubai International Cricket Stadium, Dubai

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 160

2nd innings average score: 158

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 63%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

In the previous outing between these teams, Keiron Pollard (86 off 38 and a wicket) and Rovman Powell (97 off 41) were the captain and vice-captain of the Ultimate Team respectively. While Powell has starred in the Ultimate Team in all 8 games, Pollard missed out only once.

Adam Zampa’s last 4 bowling figures read: 3 for 25, 3 for 16, 3 for 16, and 1 for 20. He has not only provided bonus points for three-wicket hauls but also for economy.

In his last 10 games, Muhammad Waseem has scored 339 runs at 38 including 3 thirties and 2 fifties.

Dwayne Bravo has bagged 2 two-fors and as many three-fors in 7 outings. As has been the case over the years, his death bowling has been exceptional.

In the last 3 games at the venue, as many as 39 sixes were hammered.

Although the pitch has been favouring batters, spinners have had their moments in the middle overs. While they took 13 wickets, pacers did their bit in the powerplay and at the death and scalped 23 wickets.
